[[File:PalpatineRepublicArmy.png|thumb|right|250px|The phrase "Palpatine's Secret Police" originated from the belief that the Jedi Order had become a secret police for Supreme Chancellor Palpatine.]]
"'''Palpatine's Secret Police'''" was a phrase that negatively described the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order's]] association with [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]-wide conflict during which the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] served as [[Jedi General/Legends|generals]] in the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]]. The phrase was in usage<ref name="YodaDR">''[[Yoda: Dark Rendezvous]]''</ref> by [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]],<ref name="Essential Reader's Companion">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> almost three [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after the [[First Battle of Geonosis/Legends|first battle]] between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]]. The phrase steadily grew in usage during the height of the [[Cloning/Legends|Clone]] Wars, especially after a number of wayward [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] withdrew from the Order. When speaking of their former comrades, these Jedi apostates referred to mainstream Jedi as "Palpatine's Secret Police."<ref name="YodaDR" />

